why: Primary baseline: gender effect on divorce probability with full controls (age dummies + child94 + dep94). N=5994 married in 1994.
Primary baseline: gender effect on marriage formation with full controls. N=4080 single in 1994.
Primary baseline: gender effect on widowhood with full controls + married94. N=10074 full sample.
Primary baseline: gender effect on married status in 1999 with full controls + married94. N=10074.
Algebraic complement of spec 1 (stay_married = 1-divorce). Coefficient is exactly negated. Grouped with G1.
No controls -- female only. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1. Tests sensitivity to control omission.
Age dummies only. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1.
Child94 only. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1.
Dep94 only. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1.
Child94 + dep94 without age dummies. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1.
Age dummies + child94 without dep94. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1.
Age dummies + dep94 without child94. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1.
Replace continuous child94 with binary has_child94 indicator. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1.
Add spouse_age94 to baseline controls. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1.
Add age_gap94 to baseline controls. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1. Identical coefficient to spec 14.
Add q (spouse-change rate) to baseline controls. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1.
No controls -- female only. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G2.
Age dummies only. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G2.
Child94 only. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G2.
Add col10 (unrelated numeric variable) to baseline controls. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G2.
Treatment changed from female to child94. Female-only subsample. Different causal object.
Treatment changed from female to child94. Male-only subsample. Different causal object.
Young married subsample (age groups 1-4). Same outcome/treatment as G1 but age dummies dropped.
Middle-aged married subsample (age groups 5-9). Same outcome/treatment as G1.
Old married subsample (age groups 10-13). Same outcome/treatment as G1.
Married with children subsample. Same outcome/treatment as G1.
Married without children subsample. Same outcome/treatment as G1.
Treatment changed from female to child94. Female-only subsample. Different causal object.
Treatment changed from female to child94. Male-only subsample. Different causal object.
Widowed-in-1994 subsample for marriage formation. Same treatment as G2 but different base population.
Single-other (never married/divorced) subsample. Same treatment as G2 different base population.
Trim youngest and oldest age groups (2-12). Same outcome/treatment as G1.
Low dependents subsample (dep94 <= 2). Same outcome/treatment as G1.
High dependents subsample (dep94 > 2). Same outcome/treatment as G1.
Treatment changed from female to married94. Female-only subsample. Different causal object.
Different outcome: change in dependents count. Not directly related to any baseline marital transition.
Different outcome: change in children count. Not directly related to any baseline marital transition.
Different outcome: indicator for gaining a child. Not a marital transition outcome.
Different outcome: indicator for losing a child. Not a marital transition outcome.
Different outcome: has child in 1999. Not a marital transition outcome.
Widowhood outcome restricted to married-in-1994 subsample. Same outcome/treatment as G3 different sample.
Algebraic complement of G2 baseline (stay_single = 1 - new_marriage). Coefficient is negated. Same sample.
Different outcome: being single-widowed in 1999. Combines marital status categories differently from baselines.
Different outcome: dependents count level in 1999. Not a marital transition variable.
Different outcome: children count level in 1999. Not a marital transition variable.
Treatment changed to continuous age. Different causal object from gender effect.
Treatment changed to q (spouse-change rate). Different causal object from gender effect.
Treatment changed to child94. Different causal object from gender effect.
Treatment changed to dep94. Different causal object from gender effect.
Treatment changed to has_child94 indicator. Different causal object from gender effect.
HC0 robust SEs. Same point estimate as G1 baseline different SE calculation.
HC2 robust SEs. Same point estimate as G1 baseline different SE calculation.
HC3 robust SEs. Same point estimate as G1 baseline different SE calculation.
Clustered SEs by age group. Same point estimate as G1 baseline different SE calculation.
Treatment changed to child94 and clustered by gender. Different treatment variable from G1.
Homoskedastic (classical) SEs. Same point estimate as G1 baseline different SE assumption.
Bootstrap SEs (200 replications). Same point estimate as G1 baseline. Note: p-value is 1.95 which appears anomalous.
Logit model for divorce. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1 different functional form.
Logit model for marriage formation. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G2 different functional form.
Logit model for widowhood. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G3 different functional form.
Probit model for divorce. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1 different functional form.
Logit model for married in 1999. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G4 different functional form.
Linear age instead of age dummies. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1 different age specification.
Quadratic age polynomial instead of age dummies. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1.
Cubic age polynomial instead of age dummies. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1.
Interaction of female*child94. Reports main effect of female which is effect for childless only -- not comparable to baseline ATE.
Log-transformed controls (log(1+child94) and log(1+dep94)). Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1.
WLS weighted by q (spouse-change rate). Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1 different weighting.
WLS weighted by dep94+1. Same outcome/treatment as G4 different weighting.
WLS weighted by child94+1. Same outcome/treatment/sample as G1 different weighting.
Placebo test: predict unrelated variable col10 with female. Not a marital transition outcome.
Placebo test: predict unrelated variable col11 with female. Not a marital transition outcome.
Placebo test: randomized gender assignment predicting divorce. Treatment is permuted.
Placebo test: randomized gender assignment predicting marriage formation. Treatment is permuted.
Diagnostic: dep94 predicting changed_spouse indicator. Different outcome and treatment from all baselines.
Interaction female*young. Reports main effect of female (effect for non-young only). Not baseline ATE.
Interaction female*middle. Reports main effect of female (effect for non-middle only). Not baseline ATE.
Interaction female*old. Reports main effect of female (effect for non-old only). Not baseline ATE.
Interaction female*dep94. Reports main effect of female (effect at dep94=0). Not baseline ATE.
Interaction female*q. Reports main effect of female (effect at q=0). Not baseline ATE.
Interaction age*child in marriage formation model. Reports main effect of female. Different model structure.
Interaction female*has_child for widowhood. Reports main effect (childless females). Not baseline ATE.
Interaction female*married94 on delta_dep. Different outcome from all baselines. Reports main effect.
Interaction young*child94. Reports main effect of female. Collinearity issue: huge coefficients on age dummies.
Interaction dep*age on delta_child. Different outcome from all baselines. Reports main effect of female.
